node.text:
House Beautiful examines the intricate creation of our hand painted St. Laurent wallpaper.
 
A splendid interpretation of the iconic 18th century Chinese wallpaper from the Paris home of Yves Saint Laurent and Pierre Berge, seen here in a timeless installation by Martyn Lawrence Bullard at Capard House in Ireland. @housebeautiful

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by de Gournay on August 19, 2021 tagging @degournay, @lemeuriceparis, and @lallyberger. May be an image of bedroom.

node.text:
Within a bedroom of Hôtel Le Meurice in Paris, Margaux Lally and Luc Berger – of the eponymous Lally & Berger studio – evoke a joyous ‘l’esprit de campagne’ overlooking the Jardin de Tuileries. Our hand painted ‘Temple Newsam’ Chinoiserie – a stylised depiction of an idyllic English garden – installed within a recessed alcove as an impressive headboard canopy. A delightful scene of springtime, hand painted upon a softly textured background of Moss Green Williamsburg.
 
@lallyberger @lemeuriceparis 
 
____________________________⁣

node.text:
Hand painted in a colourful and stylised manner with graphic details, our ‘Siam’ Chinoiserie is an animated and decorative scene depicting the lush vegetation and exotic florals of South East Asia - assorted plants and flowers indigenous to the region, filled with native birds, and executed against a lustrous mottled ground of antiqued Silver.

Lanterns by @carltondavidsonantiques 
Sconces by @beaumontandfletcher 
Console by @brownrigguk @shopatbrownrigg

node.text:
London Zoo - A vivid scene of the natural world, 'The Hunt' is our hand painted recreation of a mural that famously decorated the Los Angeles home of Marlene Dietrich. Installed here within Wild By Tart, the self styled neighbourhood restaurant envisaged by Jemima Jones and Lucy Carr-Ellison in an old parking lot a stones throw from London's Victoria station, the design enlivens the modernist, open plan interior - hand painted upon a lustrous metallic silk in Silver @wildbytart @tart_london 

____________________________⁣

node.text:
We recently added a little window to our guest loo in London. Dressed in a Marvic Textile stripe, also used for the tented ceiling in another colourway, it lets the sunshine stream in illuminating the 'Early Views of India' hand painted wallpaper. One of my all time favourites. The colourful figures and animals look so animated against the monochromatic grey shades of the landscape. 

Lights by @vaughandesigns 

____________________________⁣
